of the assassination.

applying the basic rules of criminal investigation wherein a motive is a necessary item when you reach the prosecution stage in any case to obtain a conviction.

party was that the state of Texas would be a necessary item of support in order for Kennedy to win the election.

In 1958, I believe, Mr. George Parr, who still politically ruled Duval County, managed to get his hands on some of the county's school funds.

and was indicted by a state grand jury, tried in state district court, and found guilty of felony theft of school funds, assessed the then maximum penalty for felony theft in the first defense of 10 years to be served in what was then known as the
TSPS, Texas State Prison System.
This case was put on appeal, and Parr remained free on appeal bond as the case wound its way through the Court of Criminal Appeals and would have ultimately gone to the state Supreme Court.
During the interim, the 1960 election, the President of the United States occurred, and John Fitzgerald Kennedy was elected President, and Lyndon Baines Johnson Vice President of the United States.
To the best of my recollection of what occurred,
The inauguration of Kennedy and Johnson was on or about the 12th of January, 1961.
And sometime between the middle and the end of March that same year,
George Parr received presidential pardon from John Fitzgerald Kennedy for his felony theft.
All of these matters would of necessity appear in the official records of the government of the United States and the state of Texas, official court records and so forth.
pertaining to these convictions and pardons.
Time proceeded on, and during the summer of 1963, the Democrat Party in the state of Texas became split into several different factions.
I believe there was about seven, all told.
And Lyndon Johnson, because the year of 1964 was to be a presidential election year again, and it was reported in the news media that he had had a talk with President Kennedy

and at that time, Governor John B. Conley, governor of the state of Texas, to the effect that he and Johnson and the president should come to Texas on what he termed a fence-mending tour in order to get the Democrat Party all back into one corral.
These terms are used among Texas ranchers pertaining to cattle, but Texas politicians use the same terminology pertaining to voters.
And at first, because of some incidents which had occurred in Dallas, Texas, when
Adlai E. Stevenson, Sr., a senator from the state of Illinois, and a retired general named Walker, who lived in Dallas, Texas, and several other rather prominent national figures.
The Democratic Party had attempted to make speeches in Dallas, Texas,
they received vegetables and eggs some sticks and stones directed at the speakers instead of any applause or exception of their speech also uh

so that it was published by the news media, newspapers, radio and television.

John Connolly had advised against the President and the Vice President both coming to Texas at the same time together going to various municipalities in the state on this fence mending tour because it was dangerous and especially the attitude of the people in Dallas, Texas.
But somehow Johnson, according to reports in the news media, persuaded the President and Governor Connolly that he and the President would not receive any such treatment even in Dallas.
So they decided to come to Dallas.
And immediately the news media began to publish stories about the anticipated visit of the president and the vice president, detailing when they would be in each municipality that they were to visit.
And publishing in the newspapers prominently displayed on the front pages
the planned motorcade route that they would follow through each of these municipalities as they progressed on their visitation.
These diagrams were also displayed on television quite frequently in each of these cities.
And so that it would be common knowledge to the people
who might want to have a chance to see their president and vice president and their governor all simultaneously be able to position themselves along these motorcade routes for that purpose.
Now,
Prior to becoming governor of the state of Texas, John B. Connolly served at the cabinet level in Washington, D.C. in the capacity of Secretary of the Navy.
And during that tenure, Lee Harvey Oswald received his
dishonorable discharge from the Marine Corps.
And it has been publicized considerably that Oswald had written letters to John Connolly requesting that he as Secretary of the Navy review his case
and consider an upgrade from dishonorable to something more desirable in the way of a discharge, and that Oswald was ignored by Connolly.
During the summer and early fall, while all the publicity was going around to the news media,
across the state, possibly across the country.

Pertaining to the visit of the president and vice president and the governor of these municipalities, Lee Harvey Oswald somehow, in spite of the reported sustenance of two homes, one in Fort Worth and one in Dallas,
without being employed at all, managed to defray the expense of making a trip to Mexico City.

which is the connecting bridge between Starr County, the county seat of which is Rio Grande City, and Old Mexico.
This was also alleged to have been the route that he was traced in returning from Mexico City back to Dallas.

It was reported by both the FBI and the Warren Commission that Oswald was traced to the Cuban consulate in Mexico City as well as the Russian consulate, but did not hold any conversation, transact any business with anyone
at either of these locations and return to Dallas, Texas.
There has been no mention made of any investigation which would clarify whether or not Oswald contacted anybody north of the border of Rio Grande, say in Starr County or Duval County,
en route to Mexico City is backed by either the FBI or the Warren Commission.
At the time this was all going on in 1963, George Parr's nephew, Archer Parr, was county sheriff in Starr County.

certainly not to be visiting the police station and getting well acquainted with the high ranking officials and all this.

course I have not mentioned the motive of Jack Ruby for any part in the assassination but I have known many people of many religious organizations and I have rather consistently found that there is a

decided to kill the man that was alleged to have killed us.
